The paper deals with a problem of learning an unknown distribution from noisy samples, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem involves estimating the probability of strings, which can be seen as a combinatorial problem (cs.DM) and involves the size of the support of the distribution, which can be seen as a data structure problem (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses algorithmic and sample complexity, which are topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
